    "long_instructions": "### Create Version 2\r\n\r\n**First, organize your workspace:**\r\n- Drag out a `play random` block into your workspace, but **do not** connect it under `when run`.\r\n- Take your first backtrack loop and place the whole thing inside the `play random` block floating in your workspace. \r\n\r\n**Then, code Version 2**:\r\n- Create a second backtrack for your GIF. \r\n- When you have something you like, take that code and add it inside the play random block. \r\n- Connect the `play random` block with both sets of backtracks back under `when run`. \r\n- Create a second trigger with a new sound effect to go with your new backtrack. \r\n- Press \"Run\" and practice triggering your sound effect based on which backtrack was chosen. ",
